# Command sqd

## What does this command do:

A SQL-like document editor cli

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go install github.com/overthinkinglabs/sqd@latest
For Raspberry Pi install using: GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go install github.com/overthinkinglabs/sqd@latest
For Mac install using: GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go install github.com/overthinkinglabs/sqd@latest

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/go/bin/sqd
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/go/bin/sqd
For Mac run: ~/go/bin/sqd

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/overthinkinglabs/sqd

## Command options

sqd '<QUERY>'               # run a SQL-like query against files
sqd -f <file>               # run all queries from a file
sqd -t '<QUERY>'            # transaction mode — rollback all changes on failure
sqd -v                      # print version
sqd dry '<QUERY>'           # dry-run: show what would change without modifying files
sqd dry -c '<QUERY>'        # dry-run with per-line detail (file names + modified lines)

# Columns available in SELECT / WHERE
#   name     — file name
#   content  — line content
#   *        — both name and content

# SELECT examples
sqd 'SELECT * FROM *.md WHERE content LIKE "%- [ ]%"'                    # open todos
sqd 'SELECT COUNT(*) FROM *.md WHERE content LIKE "### %"'               # count heading lines
sqd 'SELECT COUNT(name) FROM *.md WHERE content LIKE "### %"'            # count files with heading
sqd 'SELECT name FROM *.md WHERE content LIKE "- [ ]%" ORDER BY content' # sorted by content
sqd 'SELECT * FROM *.md ORDER BY content ASC, name DESC'                  # multi-column sort

# UPDATE examples
sqd 'UPDATE *.md SET content="### " WHERE content LIKE "## %"'           # bulk heading change
sqd 'UPDATE f.md SET content="new" WHERE content = "old"'                # exact match replace

# DELETE examples
sqd 'DELETE FROM *.log WHERE content LIKE "%DEBUG%"'                     # remove DEBUG log lines
